Package com.sanyavertolet.interview.ui.table

Class SpreadsheetTableModel

java.lang.Object
javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel
com.sanyavertolet.interview.ui.table.SpreadsheetTableModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, TableModel
public class SpreadsheetTableModel extends AbstractTableModel
A table model for the spreadsheet application, extending AbstractTableModel. The SpreadsheetTableModel class manages the data in the spreadsheet and interacts with the DataManager.

    • getValueAt

      public Object getValueAt(int row, int col)
      Returns the value at the specified row and column in the table. If the column is 0, the row number (1-based) is returned for row headers. Otherwise, the Data object managed by the DataManager is returned.
      Parameters:
      row - the row index of the value to retrieve.
      col - the column index of the value to retrieve.
      Returns:
      the value at the specified cell, or the row number if the column is 0.

    • isCellEditable

      public boolean isCellEditable(int row, int col)
      Returns whether the specified cell is editable. In this implementation, all cells are editable.
      Specified by:

    • setValueAt

      public void setValueAt(Object value, int row, int col)
      Sets the value at the specified cell to the provided value and also creates a new data in the DataManager.

      The value is expected to be either an instance of Data or an instance of String, otherwise nothing is done.

      Specified by:
      setValueAt in interface TableModel
      Overrides:
      setValueAt in class AbstractTableModel
      Parameters:
      value - the new value to set.
      row - the row index of the cell to update.
      col - the column index of the cell to update.

    • getColumnName

      public String getColumnName(int col)
      Returns the name of the specified column. The first column (index 0) is typically reserved for row headers and returns an empty string. For other columns, the column name is returned based on the default column naming scheme.
      Specified by:
      getColumnName in interface TableModel
      Overrides:
      getColumnName in class AbstractTableModel
      Parameters:
      col - the column index.
      Returns:
      the name of the specified column, or an empty string for the first column.
